# Inventory Count System - Cursor Project Rules

This project is an Inventory Count System built with Next.js.

## Current Mode

The project is currently in Prototype / Mock-first Development.

Main goal:

- Build visible UI first
- Build working mock flow first
- Requirements may change
- Real Express API is not ready yet
- Do not over-engineer production-grade security, offline sync, or version delta yet
- Keep code structure flexible so it can become production-ready later

## Core Stack

Use:

- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- React Server Components where suitable
- API Routes / Route Handlers
- Service layer for business logic
- Mock data first
- Later: Prisma + database
- Later: Auth.js / Microsoft Entra ID
- Later: Express API integration
- Later: Dexie.js / IndexedDB for offline draft

## Development Style

Write clean and flexible code.

Rules:

- Do not hardcode mock data inside React components
- Put mock data under `src/mock`
- Put business logic under `src/services`
- Put shared helpers under `src/lib`
- Put shared types under `src/types`
- Frontend should call API routes as if they are real production APIs
- Components should not directly mutate mock arrays
- Keep UI simple, clear, and tablet-friendly
- Add TODO comments where production hardening will be needed later

## Mock-first Rules

Use mock data and mock APIs first.

Mock data location:

```text
