## Tablet UI

Create these routes:

```text
/tablet/documents
/tablet/count/[documentId]
/tablet/count/[documentId]/summary
```

Tablet document list should show:

- document number
- document date
- branch
- status
- current version
- total line count
- counted line count
- button to open/start document

Tablet count page should show one product card at a time.

Product card shows:

- product image or No Image fallback
- product code
- product name
- barcode
- qty case input if allowCase = true
- qty pack input if allowPack = true
- qty piece input if allowPiece = true
- note input
- sync/save status

Buttons:

- Previous
- Next
- Uncounted items
- Save
- Submit to supervisor

## Unit Rules

A product may not have all units.

Examples:

- Product A has case / pack / piece
- Product B has pack / piece
- Product C has only piece

Only show inputs for allowed units.

Quantity fields:

```text
qtyCase
qtyPack
qtyPiece
totalBaseQty
```

Calculation:

```text
totalBaseQty =
  qtyCase * caseRatio +
  qtyPack * packRatio +
  qtyPiece
```

Rules:

- Quantity must not be negative
- Quantity must be integer
- Null means not counted yet
- 0 means counted but not found
- Do not default uncounted values to 0

## Auto Save Prototype

Implement basic Auto Save.

Behavior:

- When qty or note changes, call mock PATCH API
- Debounce around 800-1500ms if practical
- Show status:
  - Saving...
  - Saved
  - Save failed
  - Waiting sync
- Save only changed line
- Add `clientMutationId` to type/payload if practical, but full idempotency can be TODO for production

## Submit Prototype

Submit flow:

- User clicks submit
- Mock API changes version status to SUBMITTED
- Mock API changes document status to SUBMITTED
- Audit log is created through service
- Supervisor can see the document

Prototype does not need full offline pending sync block yet, but add TODO.

