## Recount Prototype

Request recount flow:

- Supervisor selects lines
- Supervisor enters reason
- API creates new version
- Document status becomes RECOUNT_REQUESTED
- Add audit log
- Staff can open the document again
- Prototype can copy previous entries into new version for simplicity
- Add TODO to later implement delta version and effective entry resolver

## Audit Log Prototype

Create an audit log service.

Prototype action examples:

```text
LOGIN
OPEN_DOCUMENT
START_COUNT
AUTO_SAVE_COUNT
SUBMIT_TO_SUPERVISOR
CREATE_VERSION
REQUEST_RECOUNT
APPROVE_VERSION
COMPLETE_DOCUMENT
```

Rules:

- Components should not write audit log directly
- Service/API should write audit logs
- Prototype may store audit log in mock state
- Production later must make audit log append-only

## Offline Draft Prototype

